''The Wing of Madoola'' garnered mixed reception from critics and retrospective commentarists.<ref name="FamTWoM"/><ref name="FHHtwom">{{cite magazine|url=https://archive.org/details/no.-016-1987-02-06/page/n64/mode/1up|title=Famicom Soft Scramble Cross Review: マドゥーラの翼|magazine={{ill|Famicom Hisshō Hon|lt=Famicom Hisshō Hon|ja|ファミコン必勝本}}|issue=16|publisher=[[Takarajimasha]]|date=February 6, 1987|page=63|language=ja}}</ref> Readers of ''Family Computer Magazine'' voted to give the game a 17.55 out of 30 score in a 1991 public poll.<ref name="FCMv7i9">{{cite magazine|title=Famicom ROM Cassette All Catalog '91 全787本 5月10日号特別付録 - マドゥーラの翼|magazine={{ill|Family Computer Magazine|lt=Family Computer Magazine|ja|ファミリーコンピュータMagazine}}|volume=7|issue=9|publisher=[[Tokuma Shoten]]|date=May 10, 1991|page=175|language=ja}}</ref> ''[[1Up.com]]''{{'}}s Todd Ciolek regarded Lucia as one of three "unsung" heroines from gaming's early days. Ciolek pointed out the game's difficulty however, citing the annoying enemies and undocumented continue system.<ref name="1UP">{{cite web|last=Ciolek|first=Todd|url=http://www.1up.com/do/blogEntry?bId=9110581|title=Unsung Heroines: Three Pioneers of Gaming's Early Days|work=[[1Up.com]]|publisher=[[IGN Entertainment]]|date=June 20, 2012|access-date=2023-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019222441/http://www.1up.com/do/blogEntry?bId=9110581|archive-date=2012-10-19|url-status=dead}}</ref> ''[[USgamer]]''{{'}}s Jeremy Parish labelled ''Wing of Madoola'' as one of the best [[Parallel importing in video games|import titles]] for the [[3DS Virtual Console]], calling it a decent second-rate Famicom game.<ref name="USG15MHGf3DSVC">{{cite web|last=Parish|first=Jeremy|url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/15-must-have-games-for-3ds-virtual-console|title=15 Must-Have Games for 3DS Virtual Console — Bonus: The best 3DS Virtual Console imports|work=[[USgamer]]|publisher=[[Gamer Network]]|date=May 29, 2014|access-date=2023-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704065041/http://www.usgamer.net/articles/15-must-have-games-for-3ds-virtual-console|archive-date=2014-07-04|url-status=dead}}</ref> ''[[Hardcore Gaming 101]]''{{'}}s Kurt Kalata noted the game's unrefined action, difficulty, repetitive visuals and stage layouts, average music, and clumsy nature of both the combat and RPG elements. Kalata stated that ''Madoola'' is "only really playable for those with a historical interest in [[Action role-playing game|action-RPG]]s."<ref name="TWoMhg101">{{cite web|last=Kalata|first=Kurt|url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/the-wing-of-madoola/|title=The Wing of Madoola|work=[[Hardcore Gaming 101]]|date=August 1, 2017|access-date=2023-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108014421/http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/the-wing-of-madoola/|archive-date=2018-01-08|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Legacy ==
The character of Lucia would later make appearances outside of ''The Wing of Madoola'', and became a popular [[Sunsoft]] character among Japanese retro gaming fans.<ref name="TWoMhg101"/><ref name="GamingHelltwom"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://dengekionline.com/articles/154268/|title=へべ、ルシア、ティセ…それとも!? サンソフトのキャラ人気投票の結果発表！|work=Dengeki Online|publisher=[[ASCII Media Works]]|date=October 24, 2022|access-date=2023-09-02|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221024023151/https://dengekionline.com/articles/154268/|archive-date=2022-10-24|url-status=live}}</ref> Lucia was featured in Sunsoft{{'}}s ''Sunclub'' magazine, being used on the cover of the first volume, as well as in other materials from the publication.<ref name="GamingHelltwom"/><ref name="SunclubV0">{{cite magazine|title=さんでんししあたあ（もりけん先生）|magazine=Sunclub|publisher=[[Sunsoft]]|date=1987}}</ref><ref name="SunclubV1">{{cite magazine|url=http://tad-p.hp.infoseek.co.jp/sun/gazou/sun/sun011.jpg|title=表紙イラスト (『マドゥーラの翼』ルシア)|magazine=Sunclub|volume=1|publisher=[[Sunsoft]]|date=January 1988|access-date=2023-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070326103039im_/http://tad-p.hp.infoseek.co.jp/sun/gazou/sun/sun011.jpg|archive-date=2007-03-26|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="Sunclub">{{cite magazine|url=http://tad-p.hp.infoseek.co.jp/sun/gazou/sun/sunbosyuu.jpg|title=サンソフトクラブ会員大募集！|magazine=Sunclub|publisher=[[Sunsoft]]|access-date=2023-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040814075321im_/http://tad-p.hp.infoseek.co.jp/sun/gazou/sun/sunbosyuu.jpg|archive-date=2004-08-14|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="NnMDNLD3Gum">{{cite book|url=https://www.gamingalexandria.com/fds/Nazoraa%20Land%20Dai%203%20Gou/Nazoraa%20Land%20Dai%203%20Gou%20-%20Manual.pdf|title=謎のマガジンディスク ナゾラーランド第3号|date=March 1988|publisher=[[Sunsoft]]|type=manual|access-date=2023-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180907000219/https://www.gamingalexandria.com/fds/Nazoraa%20Land%20Dai%203%20Gou/Nazoraa%20Land%20Dai%203%20Gou%20-%20Manual.pdf|archive-date=2018-09-07|url-status=live}}</ref> Lucia appeared in other titles such as ''[[Barcode World]]'' (1992), ''Shanghai Musume: Mahjong Girls'' (2011) for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] devices, and as a Symbol Art in ''[[Phantasy Star Online 2]]'' (2012).<ref name="TWoMhg101"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamebiz.jp/news/5981|title=サン電子、Androidアプリ『上海☆娘』シリーズ4タイトルの配信開始|publisher=Gamebiz|date=March 3, 2011|access-date=2023-09-02|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902172503/https://gamebiz.jp/news/5981|archive-date=2023-09-02|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="FC2">{{cite web|author=ほっとよう|url=http://sstotoyaya.blog.fc2.com/blog-entry-69.html|title=SA-064 マドゥーラの翼 (FC)|work=PSO2 SA BOX|publisher=[[FC2 (portal)|FC2]]|date=August 15, 2014|access-date=2023-09-02|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902181522/http://sstotoyaya.blog.fc2.com/blog-entry-69.html|archive-date=2023-09-02|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2009, an [[adventure game]] starring Lucia titled ''Ma○oolaEX'' was released for [[Personal computer|PC]] on the Japanese [[doujinshi]] site DLsite by Kenji Mori under his circle name M's Cafe.<ref name="TWoMhg101"/><ref name="GamingHelltwom"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Mori|first=Kenji|url=http://moriken.kalin.to/|title=「マドゥーラＥＸ」|work=M's CAFE|date=2009|access-date=2023-08-23|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091209220814/http://moriken.kalin.to/|archive-date=2009-12-09|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dlsite.com/home/work/%3D/product_id/RJ056053.html|title=Ma○oolaEX|work=DLsite|publisher=EISYS, inc.|date=2009|access-date=2023-08-23|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130715183927/https://www.dlsite.com/home/work/%3D/product_id/RJ056053.html|archive-date=2013-07-15|url-status=live}}</ref>

''The Wing of Madoola'' was featured in the Japanese TV show ''[[GameCenter CX]]'' (''Retro Game Master'').<ref name="TWoMhg101"/><ref name="Kotaku">{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Joel|url=https://kotaku.com/5836252/retro-game-master-episode-11-the-wing-of-madoola|title=Retro Game Master Episode 11: The Wing of Madoola|work=[[Kotaku]]|publisher=[[G/O Media]]|date=September 1, 2011|access-date=2023-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106224056/https://kotaku.com/5836252/retro-game-master-episode-11-the-wing-of-madoola|archive-date=2011-11-06|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2010, a doujin CD containing music from the game and ''Ma○oolaEX'' was distributed by the group Mackerel Sky at [[Comiket]], featuring a cover illustrated by Mori.<ref name="MackerelSky">{{cite web|url=http://sabao38.com/?page_id=171|title=CD|publisher=Mackerel Sky|date=2010|access-date=2023-08-29|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323010935/http://sabao38.com/?page_id=171|archive-date=2023-03-23|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="VGMdb7">{{cite web|url=https://vgmdb.net/album/22221|title=The Wing of Madoola -Flapping Wings- &#124; SABA-00003|publisher=VGMdb|access-date=2023-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221214073950/https://vgmdb.net/album/22221|archive-date=2022-12-14|url-status=live}}</ref> Mori also authored a manga spin-off called ''The Wing of Madoola Gaiden''.<ref name="TWoMhg101"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.suruga-ya.jp/product/detail/ZHORO2781|title=マドゥーラの翼外伝 誰がために|website=Suruga-ya.jp|access-date=2023-08-23|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200501171551/https://www.suruga-ya.jp/product/detail/ZHORO2781|archive-date=2020-05-01|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2014, artwork from the game was exhibited at the Digital Contents Expo in Nagoya.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/999/G999905/20141203063/|title=「デジタルコンテンツ博覧会 NAGOYA」のサン電子ブースで「サンソフトレトロ展」が開催|work=[[4Gamer.net]]|publisher=Aetas Inc.|date=December 3, 2014|access-date=2023-08-24|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814024208/https://www.4gamer.net/games/999/G999905/20141203063/|archive-date=2023-08-14|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ono|first=Norifumi|url=https://www.inside-games.jp/article/2014/12/13/83393.html|title=レ、レトロゲームがこんなに！？数々の秘蔵資料が陳列されたサンソフトレトロ展レポート|work={{ill|Inside Games|lt=Inside Games|ja|iNSIDE (ニュースサイト)}}|publisher={{ill|IID, Inc.|lt=IID, Inc.|ja|イード (企業)}}|date=December 13, 2014|access-date=2023-08-24|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521020518/https://www.inside-games.jp/article/2014/12/13/83393.html|archive-date=2022-05-21|url-status=live}}</ref>

